39 Q1. Given an array prices[] of size n denoting the cost of stock on each day, the task is to find the maximum total profit if we can buy and sell the stocks any number of times.
Note: We can only sell a stock which we have bought earlier and we cannot hold multiple stocks on any day.
Examples:
Input: prices[] = {100, 180, 260, 310, 40, 535, 695}

Solution:

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] prices = {100, 180, 260, 310, 40, 535, 695};
        System.out.println("Maximum Profit: " + getMaxProfit(prices));
    }

    public static int getMaxProfit(int[] prices) {
        int maxProfit = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i < prices.length; i++) {
            // If today's price is greater than yesterday's, add the profit
            if (prices[i] > prices[i - 1]) {
                maxProfit += prices[i] - prices[i - 1];
            }
        }
        return maxProfit;
    }
}

